# Question Answer Evaluation System

An automated student answer evaluation system that combines speech recognition, video capture, and NLP-based semantic similarity to objectively score spoken answers against a model answer — built to reduce manual grading effort and improve consistency in assessment.

🔗 **Project Link:** *http://127.0.0.1:5000/*

## Overview

Evaluating spoken or written student answers — especially in oral exams, viva-style assessments, or large classes — is traditionally done by a human grader, which is slow, doesn't scale well, and can be inconsistent across evaluators or even across a single evaluator's session.

This project automates that evaluation: it captures a student's spoken answer through audio and video in real time, transcribes the speech to text, and uses NLP-based similarity scoring to objectively measure how closely the answer matches a reference "model answer" — giving instant, consistent feedback instead of relying purely on manual grading.

## Features

- Real-time audio and video capture through a web interface
- Speech-to-text transcription of spoken answers
- NLP preprocessing pipeline: tokenization, stopword removal, and TF-IDF representation
- Cosine similarity-based scoring to measure semantic relevance and correctness of answers
- Deployed as a Flask web application for real-time evaluation
- ~20% reduction in manual evaluation response time and ~15–20% improvement in evaluation accuracy *(see [Notes on reported metrics](#notes-on-reported-metrics))*

## Tech Stack

| Category | Tools |
|---|---|
| Language | Python |
| Speech-to-Text | SpeechRecognition |
| Video Capture | OpenCV |
| NLP / Similarity | NLTK, Scikit-learn, TF-IDF, Cosine Similarity |
| Web Framework | Flask |

## Pipeline

```
Student speaks answer
        │
        ▼
Audio + Video Capture  (real-time, via web interface)
        │
        ▼
Speech-to-Text Transcription  (SpeechRecognition)
        │
        ▼
Text Preprocessing  (lowercasing → tokenization → stopword removal)
        │
        ▼
TF-IDF Vectorization  (student answer + model answer → numeric vectors)
        │
        ▼
Cosine Similarity Scoring  (0 to 1 similarity score)
        │
        ▼
Evaluation Result  (displayed via Flask web app)
```

